00:43:43.540 --> 00:43:45.280 align:middle line:90%
gives you a number.

00:43:45.280 --> 00:43:50.480 align:middle line:84%
But this thing won't work, so we
have to search it a bit harder.

00:43:50.480 --> 00:43:52.760 align:middle line:90%
So to do that, let's--

00:43:52.760 --> 00:43:57.140 align:middle line:84%
we can get some hint from
the following identity.

00:43:57.140 --> 00:44:02.490 align:middle line:84%
So let's look at what
this S dagger really is.

00:44:02.490 --> 00:44:04.470 align:middle line:84%
So let's look at the
property of S dagger.

00:44:04.470 --> 00:44:11.330 align:middle line:90%


00:44:11.330 --> 00:44:13.010 align:middle line:90%
So recall that the--

00:44:13.010 --> 00:44:17.040 align:middle line:84%
I think I erased it, so
let me just write it again.

00:44:17.040 --> 00:44:26.290 align:middle line:84%
So gamma mu dagger is equal
to gamma 0 gamma mu gamma 0.

00:44:26.290 --> 00:44:30.520 align:middle line:84%
So now, let's try to
find what mu nu dagger.

00:44:30.520 --> 00:44:32.950 align:middle line:84%
So let's write mu nu
dagger in the uniform--

00:44:32.950 --> 00:44:36.260 align:middle line:84%
so even though we
wrote it separately.

00:44:36.260 --> 00:44:39.710 align:middle line:84%
So you can easily check yourself
because of this property.

00:44:39.710 --> 00:44:45.660 align:middle line:84%
So this is just given by minus
gamma 0 sigma mu nu gamma 0.

00:44:45.660 --> 00:44:48.680 align:middle line:90%


00:44:48.680 --> 00:44:50.390 align:middle line:84%
Because this is
just a commutator,

00:44:50.390 --> 00:44:56.960 align:middle line:84%
so you can easily work it
out that you just get this.

00:44:56.960 --> 00:44:59.720 align:middle line:84%
So now we can find
what S dagger.

00:44:59.720 --> 00:45:02.450 align:middle line:90%


00:45:02.450 --> 00:45:11.050 align:middle line:84%
So S dagger is equal to
the exponential 1/2 i omega

00:45:11.050 --> 00:45:14.230 align:middle line:90%
mu nu, then sigma mu nu dagger.

00:45:14.230 --> 00:45:20.160 align:middle line:90%


00:45:20.160 --> 00:45:31.580 align:middle line:84%
And then this is equal to i
over 2 omega mu nu minus gamma 0

00:45:31.580 --> 00:45:33.920 align:middle line:90%
sigma mu nu gamma 0.

00:45:33.920 --> 00:45:43.860 align:middle line:90%


00:45:43.860 --> 00:45:50.320 align:middle line:84%
So now, if you remember, gamma
0 squared is equal to minus 1.

00:45:50.320 --> 00:45:52.030 align:middle line:84%
So whenever you have
such a situation--

00:45:52.030 --> 00:45:56.590 align:middle line:84%
and because gamma 0 squared
is equal to minus 1,

00:45:56.590 --> 00:45:58.930 align:middle line:84%
then you can actually
take the gamma 0 outside

00:45:58.930 --> 00:46:00.190 align:middle line:90%
of the exponential.

00:46:00.190 --> 00:46:09.220 align:middle line:84%
So this is actually equal to
minus gamma 0 exponential i

00:46:09.220 --> 00:46:13.260 align:middle line:84%
over q comma 0 mu
nu sigma mu nu.

00:46:13.260 --> 00:46:21.020 align:middle line:90%


00:46:21.020 --> 00:46:23.030 align:middle line:84%
So if you just think--
you do a Taylor

00:46:23.030 --> 00:46:27.500 align:middle line:84%
expansion of this
exponential, and then

00:46:27.500 --> 00:46:34.380 align:middle line:84%
when you take the power of
this, then for each term,

00:46:34.380 --> 00:46:38.740 align:middle line:84%
the gamma 0 at the end
will pair with a gamma 0

00:46:38.740 --> 00:46:41.410 align:middle line:84%
at the beginning
of the other term,

00:46:41.410 --> 00:46:44.470 align:middle line:90%
and then they give you minus 1.

00:46:44.470 --> 00:46:48.040 align:middle line:84%
And then you have only the first
gamma 0 and the last gamma 0

00:46:48.040 --> 00:46:49.180 align:middle line:90%
left.

00:46:49.180 --> 00:46:50.980 align:middle line:84%
And because that
gives a minus 1,

00:46:50.980 --> 00:46:53.620 align:middle line:84%
that changes this minus
sign to a plus sign.

00:46:53.620 --> 00:46:55.840 align:middle line:84%
So you just do a Taylor
expansion you will find here.

00:46:55.840 --> 00:47:00.010 align:middle line:90%


00:47:00.010 --> 00:47:03.590 align:middle line:84%
And now, we find
the nice relation.

00:47:03.590 --> 00:47:07.060 align:middle line:84%
So we find that this
is just minus gamma 0,

00:47:07.060 --> 00:47:11.275 align:middle line:84%
and this is just equal
to S minus 1 S gamma 0.

00:47:11.275 --> 00:47:14.590 align:middle line:90%


00:47:14.590 --> 00:47:16.890 align:middle line:84%
So we find that the
S dagger is actually

00:47:16.890 --> 00:47:19.215 align:middle line:90%
minus gamma 0 S minus 1.

00:47:19.215 --> 00:47:22.110 align:middle line:90%


00:47:22.110 --> 00:47:26.780 align:middle line:84%
Then, this tells us
from this property--

00:47:26.780 --> 00:47:32.050 align:middle line:90%


00:47:32.050 --> 00:47:37.770 align:middle line:84%
tells us that this
quantity psi dagger

00:47:37.770 --> 00:47:44.270 align:middle line:84%
gamma 0 psi should
transform as a scalar.

00:47:44.270 --> 00:47:48.390 align:middle line:90%
So now, let's take a look.

00:47:48.390 --> 00:47:51.540 align:middle line:84%
So this, when you do
a transformation--

00:47:51.540 --> 00:47:56.180 align:middle line:84%
so this gives you the
psi dagger S dagger.

00:47:56.180 --> 00:47:59.390 align:middle line:84%
Then, you have gamma
0, then you have S psi

00:47:59.390 --> 00:48:02.150 align:middle line:90%
under Lorentz transformation.

00:48:02.150 --> 00:48:04.310 align:middle line:90%
And now, you plug this into--

00:48:04.310 --> 00:48:08.480 align:middle line:84%
plug in S dagger equal
to this into here.

00:48:08.480 --> 00:48:15.220 align:middle line:84%
You just get minus
psi dagger, so this

00:48:15.220 --> 00:48:24.040 align:middle line:84%
is gamma 0 S dagger S minus 1
gamma 0, then gamma 0 S psi.

00:48:24.040 --> 00:48:27.940 align:middle line:84%
So this gives you minus 1--
cancels with the 1 here.

00:48:27.940 --> 00:48:30.075 align:middle line:90%
And the S one cancels with--

00:48:30.075 --> 00:48:37.090 align:middle line:84%
S minus 1 cancels with S, and
then you have dagger goes here.

00:48:37.090 --> 00:48:40.133 align:middle line:84%
So this actually is
Lorentz invariant.

00:48:40.133 --> 00:48:44.560 align:middle line:90%


00:48:44.560 --> 00:48:48.630 align:middle line:84%
So now, we find a nice
Lorentz invariant quantity.

00:48:48.630 --> 00:48:54.840 align:middle line:84%
So since we use
this all the time,

00:48:54.840 --> 00:48:58.275 align:middle line:84%
it's convenient to
introduce a new notation.

00:48:58.275 --> 00:49:20.880 align:middle line:90%


00:49:20.880 --> 00:49:34.620 align:middle line:84%
So now, I introduce --
convenient to introduce recall

00:49:34.620 --> 00:49:40.830 align:middle line:90%
psi bar equal to psi dagger.

00:49:40.830 --> 00:49:42.810 align:middle line:84%
So here, it's all
just clustered.

00:49:42.810 --> 00:49:48.390 align:middle line:84%
This is dagger, and it's all
just matrix manipulation.

00:49:48.390 --> 00:49:52.290 align:middle line:84%
Right now, we're considering
a classical theory,

00:49:52.290 --> 00:49:56.190 align:middle line:84%
and so it's convenient to
introduce objects like this.

00:49:56.190 --> 00:49:59.880 align:middle line:90%
And then we know that psi bar--

00:49:59.880 --> 00:50:03.200 align:middle line:90%
psi is a scalar.

00:50:03.200 --> 00:50:06.750 align:middle line:84%
So that thing just
becomes psi bar and psi.

00:50:06.750 --> 00:50:09.570 align:middle line:90%


00:50:09.570 --> 00:50:13.620 align:middle line:84%
So it's convenient
to work out the--

00:50:13.620 --> 00:50:16.980 align:middle line:84%
how psi bar
transforms by itself.

00:50:16.980 --> 00:50:20.970 align:middle line:84%
So you just use this relation
so you can check yourself.

00:50:20.970 --> 00:50:24.180 align:middle line:84%
So as an exercise for
you to check yourself

00:50:24.180 --> 00:50:27.630 align:middle line:84%
under Lorentz
transformation psi bar

00:50:27.630 --> 00:50:34.990 align:middle line:84%
x is equal to psi
bar prime x prime.

00:50:34.990 --> 00:50:38.170 align:middle line:84%
So if you go to the new
psi bar prime x prime

00:50:38.170 --> 00:50:44.410 align:middle line:90%
is equal to psi bar x S minus 1.

00:50:44.410 --> 00:50:47.245 align:middle line:84%
So you can easily check
yourself this relation.

00:50:47.245 --> 00:50:53.070 align:middle line:90%


00:50:53.070 --> 00:50:56.190 align:middle line:84%
Similarly, using
this transformation

00:50:56.190 --> 00:50:58.800 align:middle line:84%
of gamma partial
mu, you can also

00:50:58.800 --> 00:51:07.410 align:middle line:84%
check that the gamma
mu partial mu so prime

00:51:07.410 --> 00:51:16.310 align:middle line:84%
psi prime x prime equal to
S gamma mu partial mu psi.

00:51:16.310 --> 00:51:19.480 align:middle line:90%


00:51:19.480 --> 00:51:21.812 align:middle line:90%
So you can also check yourself--

00:51:21.812 --> 00:51:22.645 align:middle line:90%
check this equation.

00:51:22.645 --> 00:51:29.580 align:middle line:90%


00:51:29.580 --> 00:51:34.710 align:middle line:84%
So yeah, just by using these
properties of S dagger.

00:51:34.710 --> 00:51:37.740 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, just-- yeah, this,
you don't use the--

00:51:37.740 --> 00:51:39.690 align:middle line:84%
you only use for
