00:51:39.690 --> 00:51:42.630 align:middle line:84%
Just use how partial
mu prime transform

00:51:42.630 --> 00:51:46.080 align:middle line:84%
and how psi transform, and
then you can show this is true.

00:51:46.080 --> 00:51:51.010 align:middle line:90%


00:51:51.010 --> 00:51:53.000 align:middle line:90%
Good.

00:51:53.000 --> 00:51:57.190 align:middle line:84%
So this-- also this
gamma mu partial mu

00:51:57.190 --> 00:52:01.130 align:middle line:84%
will appear a lot because this
appears in the Dirac equation.

00:52:01.130 --> 00:52:05.620 align:middle line:84%
So it's convenient to
introduce a new notation.

00:52:05.620 --> 00:52:14.170 align:middle line:84%
Say gamma mu partial mu we
define to be partial slash.

00:52:14.170 --> 00:52:19.600 align:middle line:84%
So essentially, anything
slash corresponding

00:52:19.600 --> 00:52:21.400 align:middle line:84%
to that thing contract
with gamma mu.

00:52:21.400 --> 00:52:24.750 align:middle line:90%


00:52:24.750 --> 00:52:26.340 align:middle line:84%
And then this
equation then can be

00:52:26.340 --> 00:52:32.460 align:middle line:84%
