01:04:45.045 --> 01:04:54.510 align:middle line:90%


01:04:54.510 --> 01:05:06.190 align:middle line:90%
So this is [INAUDIBLE].

01:05:06.190 --> 01:05:09.640 align:middle line:84%
So now, we have
classical solutions.

01:05:09.640 --> 01:05:19.300 align:middle line:90%


01:05:19.300 --> 01:05:26.440 align:middle line:84%
So by construction, the
Dirac equation has solutions.

01:05:26.440 --> 01:05:29.620 align:middle line:90%


01:05:29.620 --> 01:05:31.660 align:middle line:84%
We know must be
proportional to e to the i k

01:05:31.660 --> 01:05:38.470 align:middle line:84%
x with k squared equal
to minus m squared.

01:05:38.470 --> 01:05:39.670 align:middle line:90%
So this is by construction.

01:05:39.670 --> 01:05:45.680 align:middle line:84%
Because we square it, we get
the Klein-Gordon equation.

01:05:45.680 --> 01:05:52.060 align:middle line:84%
So this k mu would
be omega k and k.

01:05:52.060 --> 01:05:56.870 align:middle line:90%


01:05:56.870 --> 01:06:01.760 align:middle line:84%
But this is not enough
because the Dirac equation--

01:06:01.760 --> 01:06:04.940 align:middle line:84%
because psi have
four components.

01:06:04.940 --> 01:06:08.220 align:middle line:84%
So this just determines
one factor of it.

01:06:08.220 --> 01:06:10.550 align:middle line:84%
And we also have
to determine it's--

01:06:10.550 --> 01:06:14.180 align:middle line:84%
the behavior of all
its four components.

01:06:14.180 --> 01:06:18.990 align:middle line:84%
And so now, that's we
are going to do now.

01:06:18.990 --> 01:06:22.770 align:middle line:84%
So we will separate the
solutions into two types.

01:06:22.770 --> 01:06:27.870 align:middle line:84%
So one type is we call psi
plus x, which corresponding

01:06:27.870 --> 01:06:33.760 align:middle line:90%
to uk x, the expression ik x.

01:06:33.760 --> 01:06:37.850 align:middle line:84%
And another we call
the psi minus x,

01:06:37.850 --> 01:06:40.900 align:middle line:90%
which corresponding to vk x.

01:06:40.900 --> 01:06:42.400 align:middle line:90%
vk-- yeah, sorry--

01:06:42.400 --> 01:06:45.680 align:middle line:90%
no x-- because it's minus ik x.

01:06:45.680 --> 01:06:49.950 align:middle line:90%


01:06:49.950 --> 01:06:53.550 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, so uk vk,
they just-- they're

01:06:53.550 --> 01:06:59.280 align:middle line:84%
all four-component spinors which
have the same thing as psi,

01:06:59.280 --> 01:07:01.240 align:middle line:84%
because this is
just some number.

01:07:01.240 --> 01:07:03.720 align:middle line:90%
So because this is--

01:07:03.720 --> 01:07:07.528 align:middle line:84%
because k have the
positive frequency,

01:07:07.528 --> 01:07:09.945 align:middle line:84%
so this is some kind of--
called positive energy solution.

01:07:09.945 --> 01:07:14.820 align:middle line:90%


01:07:14.820 --> 01:07:18.960 align:middle line:84%
And this is called the
negative energy solution.

01:07:18.960 --> 01:07:22.410 align:middle line:84%
But it's the same thing
as in the scalar case.

01:07:22.410 --> 01:07:25.568 align:middle line:84%
They don't really--
there's not really--

01:07:25.568 --> 01:07:27.360 align:middle line:84%
when we quantize the
theory, there's really

01:07:27.360 --> 01:07:31.770 align:middle line:90%
no negative energy excitations.

01:07:31.770 --> 01:07:33.360 align:middle line:90%
It's just a name.

01:07:33.360 --> 01:07:36.330 align:middle line:84%
So we call the positive
energy and negative energy

01:07:36.330 --> 01:07:37.350 align:middle line:90%
just a name.

01:07:37.350 --> 01:07:39.120 align:middle line:84%
So the actual
physical excitations

01:07:39.120 --> 01:07:42.240 align:middle line:90%
always have positive energy.

01:07:42.240 --> 01:07:52.890 align:middle line:84%
And this uk and vk, they are all
four-component complex vectors.

01:07:52.890 --> 01:08:01.420 align:middle line:90%


01:08:01.420 --> 01:08:02.080 align:middle line:90%
Yes?

01:08:02.080 --> 01:08:08.140 align:middle line:84%
STUDENT: So it seems like the
