01:08:13.990 --> 01:08:16.165 align:middle line:84%
Indeed, we should
label them by k.

01:08:16.165 --> 01:08:19.649 align:middle line:90%


01:08:19.649 --> 01:08:20.149 align:middle line:90%
Good.

01:08:20.149 --> 01:08:24.050 align:middle line:84%
So this-- so
essentially, we just--

01:08:24.050 --> 01:08:26.029 align:middle line:84%
in the scalar case,
you just expand it

01:08:26.029 --> 01:08:29.640 align:middle line:84%
in terms of plane wave, and
then you just get some constant.

01:08:29.640 --> 01:08:33.390 align:middle line:84%
So here, its a little bit
indicate we have a vector.

01:08:33.390 --> 01:08:35.016 align:middle line:84%
Now, we need to
solve these vectors.

01:08:35.016 --> 01:08:36.599 align:middle line:84%
So our goal is to
solve these vectors.

01:08:36.599 --> 01:08:39.609 align:middle line:90%


01:08:39.609 --> 01:08:42.640 align:middle line:84%
And then you just plug them
into the Dirac equation.

01:08:42.640 --> 01:08:45.080 align:middle line:84%
Just plug these two
into the Dirac equation,

01:08:45.080 --> 01:08:52.149 align:middle line:84%
and then you get the equations
for the uk and the vk.

01:08:52.149 --> 01:08:55.450 align:middle line:84%
And I will also
suppress the k in the uv

01:08:55.450 --> 01:08:59.470 align:middle line:84%
and v just for
notational simplicity.

01:08:59.470 --> 01:09:02.920 align:middle line:90%
So when you have the gamma mu--

01:09:02.920 --> 01:09:06.430 align:middle line:84%
partial mu minus
m, psi equal to 0,

01:09:06.430 --> 01:09:09.490 align:middle line:84%
you just plug the
psi plus minus m,

01:09:09.490 --> 01:09:14.500 align:middle line:84%
and then you find that the
following equations for u

01:09:14.500 --> 01:09:19.450 align:middle line:84%
if you get i k slash
minus m u equal to 0,

01:09:19.450 --> 01:09:24.890 align:middle line:84%
and the i k slash
and the minus--

01:09:24.890 --> 01:09:27.560 align:middle line:84%
yeah, I think-- let me
just double-check the sign.

01:09:27.560 --> 01:09:28.970 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, indeed.

01:09:28.970 --> 01:09:34.490 align:middle line:84%
So you get i k slash
plus m V equal to 0.

01:09:34.490 --> 01:09:36.510 align:middle line:90%
So you get these two equations.

01:09:36.510 --> 01:09:39.500 align:middle line:84%
So our goal is just to
solve those equations.

01:09:39.500 --> 01:09:46.680 align:middle line:84%
And the k slash, just as
defined before, it just

01:09:46.680 --> 01:09:52.356 align:middle line:84%
defines as in the partial slash
k slash equal to mu gamma.

01:09:52.356 --> 01:09:58.080 align:middle line:90%


01:09:58.080 --> 01:09:59.610 align:middle line:90%
Good.

01:09:59.610 --> 01:10:02.120 align:middle line:84%
So you can also work out
the complex conjugate.

01:10:02.120 --> 01:10:06.230 align:middle line:84%
So let me just write
down the equations,

01:10:06.230 --> 01:10:08.960 align:middle line:84%
because sometimes they
will be used later.

01:10:08.960 --> 01:10:14.750 align:middle line:84%
So the u bar i k slash
minus m equal to 0,

01:10:14.750 --> 01:10:15.980 align:middle line:90%
the complex conjugate.

01:10:15.980 --> 01:10:20.000 align:middle line:90%
And v bar i k slash plus m.

01:10:20.000 --> 01:10:33.480 align:middle line:90%


01:10:33.480 --> 01:10:41.770 align:middle line:84%
So now, let's try to work
out the uk and the vk

01:10:41.770 --> 01:10:45.450 align:middle line:90%
by solving those equations.

01:10:45.450 --> 01:10:50.830 align:middle line:90%
So we do this by--

01:10:50.830 --> 01:10:54.890 align:middle line:84%
you can, in principle,
do it by brute force.

01:10:54.890 --> 01:10:57.360 align:middle line:90%
So after all, you just--

01:10:57.360 --> 01:10:59.760 align:middle line:90%
these are just 4x4 equations--

01:10:59.760 --> 01:11:02.940 align:middle line:90%
4x4 matrix equations.

01:11:02.940 --> 01:11:04.200 align:middle line:90%
Just linear algebra.

01:11:04.200 --> 01:11:08.470 align:middle line:84%
You can-- in principle,
we can solve it.

01:11:08.470 --> 01:11:11.580 align:middle line:84%
But the physicists are
often lazy, so we often--

01:11:11.580 --> 01:11:14.610 align:middle line:84%
still even for the
problem, you can solve--

01:11:14.610 --> 01:11:16.650 align:middle line:90%
we still look for shortcuts.

01:11:16.650 --> 01:11:19.570 align:middle line:84%
And so in this case, there
are two possible shortcuts.

01:11:19.570 --> 01:11:23.310 align:middle line:84%
There are two possible
ways we can do, and so

01:11:23.310 --> 01:11:26.110 align:middle line:90%
