01:12:03.750 --> 01:12:12.638 align:middle line:84%
i m gamma 0 minus m
u equal to 0 and i

01:12:12.638 --> 01:12:18.740 align:middle line:90%
m gamma 0 plus m v equal to 0.

01:12:18.740 --> 01:12:21.700 align:middle line:90%


01:12:21.700 --> 01:12:23.350 align:middle line:90%
I think-- do I--

01:12:23.350 --> 01:12:28.590 align:middle line:90%


01:12:28.590 --> 01:12:31.770 align:middle line:90%
so I think the mu--

01:12:31.770 --> 01:12:32.520 align:middle line:90%
oh, yeah.

01:12:32.520 --> 01:12:38.561 align:middle line:84%
Sorry, I should have a minus
sign here because of the--

01:12:38.561 --> 01:12:41.840 align:middle line:90%
it's the k upper index.

01:12:41.840 --> 01:12:44.750 align:middle line:84%
So it's the k upper
index equal to omega.

01:12:44.750 --> 01:12:47.900 align:middle line:84%
Then k lower index
equal to minus omega.

01:12:47.900 --> 01:12:51.310 align:middle line:90%


01:12:51.310 --> 01:12:53.440 align:middle line:84%
And here, when we
contract with gamma 0,

01:12:53.440 --> 01:12:56.030 align:middle line:84%
